ability have turned into a politicised currency both for addressing and obscuring asymmetries of power, and how media activism and state policies address so-called vulnerable groups. Taking on such heated topics as trigger warnings and diversity policies, the book will be of interest to scholars and students in media and cultural studies, affect theory, gender studies, queer theory and critical race studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aactivism.  aaffect.  abody.  acritical race studies.  acultural policy.  afeminism.  amedia.  aqueer theory.  asexuality.  avulnerability.1 aAhmed, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrunow, Dagmar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGondouin, Johanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHabel, Ylva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalberstam, Jack, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorak, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoivunen, Anu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoivunen, Anu, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKyrölä, Katariina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKyrölä, Katariina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLee Gerdén, Mara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaasonen, Susanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRyberg, Ingrid, e